s as well as to students and lecturers specialising in film studies or French studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2020. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh  aAmerican underground.  aArte povera.  aGuy Debord.  aJean Eustache.  aMay 68.  aNew Wave.  aPolitical cinema.  aPost-New Wave.  aSituationists.  aSurrealism.1 aLeonard, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611596640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526115966423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526115966/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles